CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 10, 1958, page A14, reads: "Gay Northeasterners Plan Confab - Members of the Pittsburgh chapter of the Gay Northeasterners (there are seven chapters in all) are ready for the national gathering which will take over the social scene May 30-June 1. Glittering plans are in order for the delegates and members who make Pittsburgh the focal point for fun and festivity that important week-end. Pictured are chairmen of the various committees. Left to right, front row: Mmes. Alyce Woodruff, Mary McEinheimer [McEnheimer], Julia Gaines, Helen Prattis and Virginia Carter Lowe. Second row: Mmes. Marian Holmes, Eloise Page and Margaret Jane Smith. Top row: Mmes. Easter Little, Thelma Allen and Elizabeth Henderson. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Members of Pittsburgh Chapter of Gay Northeasterners, front row from left: Alyce Woodruff, Mary McEnheimer, Julia Gaines, Helen Prattis, Virginia Carter Lowe; second row: Marian Holmes, Eloise Page, Margaret Jane Smith; top row: Easter Little, Thelma Allen, and Elizabeth Henderson, posed on stairs at Greene Hearth
